Description:
   Duty Strike is the foundational combat technique of the Registry School
   curriculum — a direct, committed blow delivered from a stable stance. In
   Dunmar's Watch doctrine the first blow from held ground is not an attack;
   it is a statement of position. The duty strike forces the enemy to
   acknowledge that the ground is held.

   Damage is calculated from pseudo-level and Strength, same as other Warden
   melee attacks (kick, checkpoint break). This is not a finesse technique;
   it is weight and commitment delivered correctly.

   Syntax: duty strike <target>
   Requires POS_FIGHTING. Can be practiced to improve hit rate.
